      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:1:2:3",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُهُ يَقُولُ سَعِدَ امْرُؤٌ لَمْ يَمُتْ حَتَّى يَرَى خَلَفاً مِنْ نَفْسِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Salma Bin Al Khattab, from Al Hassan Bin Ali Bin Yaqteen, from Yunus Bin Yaqoub, from a man, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I heard him<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘Happiness of a person is that he does not die until he sees a successor from himself’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Salmah ibn al-Khattab from al-Hassan ibn Ali ibn Yaqtin from Yunus ibn Ya’qub from a man who has said the following: “I once heard abu al-Hassan, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ‘Fortunate is the man who does not die before seeing a successor of his own self.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
